## 4. Component Standards

### 4.1 Buttons

**Primary Button:**
```css
.btn-primary {
  background: var(--ns-accent);
  color: var(--ns-white);
  padding: var(--ns-space-3) var(--ns-space-6);
  border-radius: var(--ns-radius-md);
  font-weight: 500;
}
```

**Secondary Button:**
```css
.btn-secondary {
  background: transparent;
  color: var(--ns-accent);
  border: 1px solid var(--ns-accent);
  padding: var(--ns-space-3) var(--ns-space-6);
  border-radius: var(--ns-radius-md);
  font-weight: 500;
}
```

**Button Rules:**
- Clear, action-oriented labels
- Adequate touch target (44px minimum on mobile)
- Consistent styling across site
- No more than 2 button styles per page

### 4.2 Cards

```css
.card {
  background: var(--ns-white);
  border: 1px solid var(--ns-gray-300);
  border-radius: var(--ns-radius-lg);
  padding: var(--ns-space-6);
}

.card-elevated {
  box-shadow: 0 4px 6px -1px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.1);
  border: none;
}
```

**Card Rules:**
- Consistent padding
- Clear visual hierarchy within cards
- Don't overload with information
- Use elevation sparingly

### 4.3 Forms

```css
.input {
  background: var(--ns-white);
  border: 1px solid var(--ns-gray-300);
  border-radius: var(--ns-radius-md);
  padding: var(--ns-space-3) var(--ns-space-4);
  font-size: var(--ns-text-base);
}

.input:focus {
  border-color: var(--ns-accent);
  outline: none;
  box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px var(--ns-accent / 0.1);
}
```

**Form Rules:**
- Clear labels above inputs
- Helpful placeholder text (not as labels)
- Visible focus states
- Inline validation where appropriate

